\par
\b Training and Validation Loss Behaviour\par
\b0\par
The training and validation loss curves for Model 2 show stronger learning behaviour than the baseline model. Training loss decreases from approximately 0.0927 at epoch 1 to about 0.0368 at epoch 100. Validation loss also declines from around 0.0707 to about 0.0381 by the end of training. Compared with the baseline model, the final training and validation losses are lower, which suggests that the additional bottleneck layer improves feature refinement.\par
\par
The training process is stable overall, with some temporary fluctuations in validation loss at intermediate stages. These variations are not severe enough to indicate instability. Instead, they reflect the typical behaviour of a deeper model responding to data complexity while still converging properly. The close relationship between the final training and validation loss values suggests that the model generalises well and does not show strong overfitting. The bottleneck therefore appears to improve learning capacity without causing optimisation problems.\par
\par
