\par
\b Inference from the PSNR and SSIM Curves\par
\b0\par
The metric curves suggest that Model 2 improves reconstruction quality more effectively than the baseline. The rise in PSNR and SSIM supports the interpretation that the bottleneck helps the network form a better latent representation before decoding. This makes Model 2 a stronger conventional CNN model than Model 1.\par
\par
\b 3.3.3.3 Hybrid CNN Model\par
\b0\par
The third model is the hybrid CNN architecture used as the most advanced variant in this study. It combines convolutional encoder-decoder processing with a MobileViT-style bottleneck, skip connections, and a residual output connection. The encoder extracts low-level and mid-level features, the MobileViT-style bottleneck models deeper contextual relationships at a compressed resolution, and the decoder reconstructs the enhanced image while recovering spatial information. Skip connections link encoder features to decoder stages so that fine details are preserved, while the residual output adds the input image back before the sigmoid activation to encourage restoration rather than complete re-synthesis.\par
\par
Because this model integrates local convolutional processing with transformer-style contextual modelling, it is expected to improve perceptual enhancement quality and structural consistency. It is more expressive than the previous two architectures, although it is also more computationally demanding.\par
\par
\b [Insert Model 3 Block Diagram Here]\par
\b0 Suggested file: results/model_block_diagrams/model3_block_diagram.png\par
\par
\b Training and Validation Curves\par
\b0\par
The hybrid model shows stable training behaviour under the combined loss setting. The training loss decreases from approximately 0.0927 in the early stage to about 0.0513 near epoch 100, while the validation loss decreases from roughly 0.0707 to around 0.0465. Although the loss values are not directly comparable to the simpler models on a one-to-one basis because the hybrid model is trained with the combined L1, Edge, and Color objective, the downward trend clearly indicates that optimisation is effective and the network is learning.\par
\par
The validation loss remains consistently below or close to the training loss near later epochs, which is reasonable because training uses augmentation while validation is measured on clean held-out paired samples. This pattern does not suggest harmful overfitting. Instead, it indicates that the model learns robust enhancement behaviour while maintaining stable validation performance. The training process therefore appears well controlled even though the model itself is more complex than the earlier CNN variants.\par
\par
