\b Interpretation of the Hybrid Model Curves\par
\b0\par
The hybrid model benefits from stronger feature modelling capacity. Even though its loss formulation is more complex, the overall trends remain smooth and convergent. This indicates that the architecture is trainable and that the hybrid bottleneck, skip connections, and residual design work together effectively. In the final EUVP comparison, this model also produces the strongest no-reference quality scores and the highest SSIM, which supports the conclusion that the hybrid design improves perceptual enhancement and structural preservation.\par
\par
\b Performance Summary Across the Three Models\par
\b0\par
Using the saved EUVP comparison results, the baseline model achieved UCIQE 5.7979, UIQM 0.6031, PSNR 26.1530, and SSIM 0.8544. The CNN with bottleneck improved these values to UCIQE 6.0396, UIQM 0.6297, PSNR 26.5912, and SSIM 0.8592. The hybrid model achieved the strongest no-reference metrics and the highest SSIM, with UCIQE 6.4122, UIQM 0.6757, PSNR 23.7551, and SSIM 0.8639. These results show that the hybrid design is the strongest in perceptual underwater enhancement quality, while Model 2 remains strongest in PSNR.\par
